      "id": 73556,
      "title": "Overview",
      "content": "<h1>Enigma Codabench Competition</h1>\n\n<p>\nThis competition is for internal evaluation of models on acquired datasets.\n</p>\n\n<p>\nThe goal for this competition phase is to predict actual neural responses given video and gaze data from each of four Macaque fixed-gaze recording sessions.\n</p>\n\n<p>\nTo participate:\n\t\n1. Sign up for a free Codabench account.\n2. Join our competition <a href=\"https://www.codabench.org/competitions/10814/?secret_key=372c2844-5403-41e6-ad2c-\n\t2d6b755f2d3f\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here</a>.\n3. Submit predictions and add to leaderboard.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  <a href=\"\thttps://github.com/enigma-brain/monkey-baselines/tree/jb_update_for_codabench/codabench\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n  Starter notebooks in the \"jb-update-for-codabench\" branch of the <code>monkey-baselines</code> repo\n  </a> provide a walkthrough of toy examples of model training and model inference on the Codabench datasets, as well as submitting model predictions to the Codabench site. To view these, please request access to the repository from Konstantin or Federico.\n</p>",
      "index": 0
    }
